# Commit and PR policy (org)

## Commits

- **Only commit when the user asks**, or when the task explicitly includes committing (e.g. SDLC slice, "commit this").
- When committing: imperative message, 1–2 sentences on *why*; one concern per commit when practical (code / tests / docs separate).
- Never force-push `main`; never skip hooks unless user requests.

## Pull requests

- One feature or theme per PR when possible.
- **Summary** (2–4 bullets) + **Test plan** checklist.
- Call out breaking changes, migrations, and manual verification steps.
- Avoid unrelated refactors in the same PR.

Use `gh` for GitHub operations when creating PRs.
